FBIS4-38428 "drsov104_b_94023" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 31 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Dubinin Praises Latest Economic Edicts Dubinin Praises Latest Economic Edicts LD3105093494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0605 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105093494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] The Russian Federation's Acting Finance Minister Sergey Dubinin described the latest economic edicts issued by the Russian president as a timely step aimed at establishing order in the financial sphere. He said these edicts were drafted by the Finance Ministry in conjunction with other bodies, including the Russian Central Bank, the State Tax Service, and the Economics Ministry. Sergey Dubinin believes that the presidential decrees will help solve a whole range of problems to do with the revenue part of the state budget, in particular through the better collection of taxes. Implementation of these documents will make it possible to step up, at least in part, the solution of the problem of nonpayments. In addition, the edicts are targeted at improving financial discipline in general.
